<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3637.4.1>
    bibo:endPage "411" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "401" ;
    bibo:volume "3637" ;
    dc:creator "Morgan, David L.; Beatty, Stephen J.; Adams, Mark" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Nannoperca pygmaea, a new species of pygmy perch (Teleostei: Percichthyidae) from Western Australia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221644>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221645>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221646>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221647> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221644>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Percichthyidae of the South West Coastal Drainage Division, Western Australia. A. Nannoperca pygmaea sp. nov. (WAM P. 33380 – 001, 31.8 mm SL). B. Nannoperca vittata. C. Nannatherina balstoni. D. Bostockia porosa. Bottom, holotype N. pygmaea sp. nov. Photographs S. Beatty and D. Morgan." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221645>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Principal Co-ordinates Analysis (PCA) of Nannoperca vittata from six river systems (Mitchell (Hay) River, Marbelup Brook, King River, Kalgan River, Angove River, Goodga River) and Nannoperca pygmaea genotyped in the allozyme study. The relative PCA scores have been plotted for the first (X-axis) and second (Y-axis) dimensions, which individually explained 65 % and 9 %, respectively, of the total multivariate variation. See Fig. 1 for site localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221645/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221646>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. NJ tree based on pairwise Nei Ds among sties for Nannoperca vittata in seven catchments (Angove River, Goodga River, King River, Mitchell / Hay River, Kalgan River, Quickup River and Marbelup Brook) and Nannoperca pygmaea in the Mitchell / Hay River. See Fig. 1 for site localities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.221647>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Type locality of Nannoperca pygmaea at the confluence of the Mitchell and Hay Rivers." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/221647/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

